column7: Then agreed with Negro Luke blacksmith to do my smiths work this ^ musings^ aft the old Estes, for corn at 12lb # barrel
By cash pd Benedict the Miller
By cash to Charles the Carpenter for Mill
To Carpenter Charels two months work
By do to Tom for showing Jerry how to temper axes
By work done by Old Billy ^for Mill^ rounds
Due from Willm Pollock for 4 months hire of Patrick (Negro, blacksmith) @26 p year

Item, Due to Patrick by an order of Saml. & Jas. Fulton on me

Charles a blackman from St. Thomas Manor built a wind-mill for me in the year 1826 and completed her the first of octr he had no instrucitons from anyone. she is well built and appears to answer well.
